# Sentry crash reporting — optional, disabled unless a DSN is set here at build time.
#
# amont only reports crashes when a DSN is baked into the build. Builds from source have none
# (this example file is never read), so they send nothing — that is the default.
#
# This file is for LOCAL testing only: copy it to `.env` (gitignored) and set your DSN below,
# then `pnpm dev` / `pnpm build`. Official release builds get the DSN from CI instead — a
# `SENTRY_DSN` repository variable, mapped in .github/workflows/release.yml — so it never needs
# to live in a committed file.
#
# Reports are opt-out at runtime from the home screen; they carry no repository contents,
# diffs, or credentials, and no PII (IP, hostname, user identity).
MAIN_VITE_SENTRY_DSN=
